sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Alice
    participant S as Server
    participant B as Bob

    Note over A,B: Normal sync
    A->>S: sync(events=[a:0,a:1], frontiers=[a:1])
    S->>B: sync(events=[a:0,a:1], frontiers=[a:1])
    B->>S: sync(events=[b:0], frontiers=[a:1,b:0])
    S->>A: sync(events=[b:0], frontiers=[a:1,b:0])

    Note over A,B: Message lost! Bob doesn't receive a:2
    A->>S: sync(events=[a:2], frontiers=[a:2,b:0])
    S--xB: ✗ lost

    Note over A,B: Bob sends his frontiers → server detects gap
    B->>S: sync(events=[], frontiers=[a:1,b:0])
    Note over S: Bob has a:1 but a:2 exists → resend
    S->>B: sync(events=[a:2], frontiers=[a:2,b:0])
    Note over A,B: Bob catches up ✅
